    {
      "title": "More checking-corection data can continuously\nimprove the reasoning capability of LLMs.\nUnlike previous experiments, we use the full\nGSM8K training dataset and add our own checking-\ncorrection data. We aim to see how increasing\nchecking-correction data affects the model's rea-\nsoning, keeping the original reasoning data the\nsame. We adhere to the optimal ratio of Path\u2713 and\nPath\u00d7 ascertained from preceding experiments.\nFig. 4 shows that both direct and self-corrected\nreasoning improve as we increase the checking-\ncorrection data.",
      "heading_level": null,
      "page_id": 7,
      "polygon": [
